programme.desc: Round-up of national and international news, plus the latest from the money markets(n)

programme.title: Saturday Kitchen Live
programme.desc: Chefs Nathan Outlaw and Dan Barber join guest host Angela Hartnett to prepare more culinary treats in the kitchen, while Susie Barrie picks out wines to accompany the studio dishes(n)

programme.title: Mary Berry Everyday
programme.desc: The food writer and former Great British Bake Off judge continues to celebrate the everyday food and ingredients she has always loved, from hearty and wholesome ideas to easy-to-make crowd-pleasers and family classics. In this edition, Mary focuses on food that exemplifies indulgence, demonstrating mouth-watering dishes that give the mundane a lift with lashings of naughtiness. Treats are in store as she investigates the history of the British pie and reveals the secrets to making an easy sticky toffee pudding(n)

programme.desc: Dan Walker and guests review the week's headlines and look ahead to forthcoming fixtures, as the Premier League takes a backseat and World Cup qualifiers take centre stage(n)

programme.title: Money for Nothing
programme.desc: Entrepreneur Sarah Moore saves a chair, some bits of hawthorn wood, an old art deco style toy and a broken table from the nation's tips. She then sets about transforming them, with the help of three talented artisans, into brand new items ready to be put up for sale(n)

programme.title: Bargain Hunt
programme.desc: Jonathan Pratt and David Harper offer advice to two teams of antiques-hunters at the Staffordshire County Showground. Presenter Tim Wonnacott visits Georgian town house No 1 Royal Crescent in Bath(n)

programme.title: Escape to the Country
programme.desc: A Hertfordshire couple go house-hunting in Lincolnshire with a budget of £375,000. Jonnie Irwin tries to find them a character property, and experiences a miniature motoring icon(n)

programme.title: Wallace & Gromit: A Matter of Loaf and Death
programme.desc: The duo open their own bakery, Top Bun, and business is soon booming - not least because a `cereal killer' is targeting all the rival bakers in town. Even better, Wallace has caught the eye of local beauty Piella Bakewell. But Gromit is more concerned that his master might become the killer's next victim. With the voices of Peter Sallis and Sally Lindsay(n)

programme.title: Brave
programme.desc: A princess defies her mother's plans to secure peace by marrying her off to the son of one of their allies. A witch provides the rebellious royal with a magic spell to change her fate, but the enchantment backfires disastrously when the queen is transformed into a bear. Pixar's animated fantasy, with the voices of Kelly Macdonald, Emma Thompson and Billy Connolly(n)

programme.title: Who Dares Wins
programme.desc: Game show in which Nick Knowles challenges two pairs of complete strangers to team up, with each pair battling to outdo the other by listing as much as they know about a given subject. The first couple to win two rounds get to play for £50,000 and each time the champions defeat a new set of opponents their winnings mount up(n)

programme.title: Pointless Celebrities
programme.desc: Alexander Armstrong quizzes eight comedians who hope they can think of the answers no one else could. The duos are Hal Cruttenden and Justin Moorhouse, Rhona Cameron and Sean Hughes, Jeremy Hardy and Francesca Martinez, and Robert Webb and Isy Suttie. Richard Osman tells them where they've gone wrong(n)

programme.title: Let's Sing and Dance for Comic Relief
programme.desc: After three weeks of enthusiastic mimicry, the comedy-themed musical talent show draws to a close. Mel Giedroyc and Sue Perkins are on hand to present a live grand final, in which the six most popular celebrity performers from the previous three rounds battle it out. Back on March 4, first-round judges Katharine Ryan, Jo Brand and Frank Skinner were suitably impressed by Sara Pascoe's acrobatic turn as Chandelier singer Sia, while the public were wowed by Rickie Haywood and Melvin Odoom's 1990s-era Will Smith medley. These two acts became the first to grab a confirmed place in the final, and tonight, they perform alongside their rivals from successive weeks to determine which off-beat performance will ultimately be named the winner. Taking a seat on the panel this week are Rufus Hound, Katy Brand and Jason Manford, while Zara Larsson and Dua Lipa perform. Last in the series(n)

programme.title: Casualty
programme.desc: Robyn is feeling positive following the premature arrival of her daughter Charlotte. However, it seems she is failing to grasp the seriousness of her baby's illness. As the child's condition worsens, Robyn struggles to decide whether to follow her head or her heart in authorising treatment. Meanwhile, Cal tries to find a way to ease the passing of Miriam, an elderly woman with end-stage lung cancer, but trouble arises when Miriam's daughter Neeve registers a complaint against him for prolonging her mother's suffering(n)

programme.title: All Round to Mrs Brown's
programme.desc: Mrs Brown's Boys creator, writer and star Brendan O'Carroll dons Agnes's famous cardigan and curlers once again, throwing open the doors of the larger-than-life Irish matriarch's home to host a Saturday night chat show, filmed in front of a live studio audience. She begins by inviting actress Pamela Anderson, tennis coach Judy Murray and entertainments manager and TV personality Louis Walsh, among others to join her in the sitting room(n)

programme.title: Pirates of the Caribbean: At World's End
programme.desc: The swashbuckling rogues join forces with old foe Barbossa to take on villainous Lord Beckett. But first they have to journey to the ends of the Earth to free Captain Jack Sparrow from his hellish imprisonment in Davy Jones' Locker. Fantasy adventure sequel, starring Johnny Depp, Geoffrey Rush, Orlando Bloom, Keira Knightley and Chow Yun-Fat, and featuring a cameo appearance by Keith Richards(n)

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two(n)

programme.title: A to Z of TV Gardening
programme.desc: Carol Kirkwood looks at subjects beginning with the letter H, visiting the Hyacinth National Collection, before Monty Don demonstrates how to plant the bulbs. Plus, a look at keeping hens(n)

programme.title: A Damsel in Distress
programme.desc: The servants of an aristocratic English family place bets on who their employers' daughter will marry. A footman has his money on an unexpected stranger, so convinces an American singer that she is madly in love with him. Musical comedy adapted by PG Wodehouse from his own novel, starring Fred Astaire and Joan Fontaine and featuring songs by George and Ira Gershwin(n)

programme.title: Hue and Cry
programme.desc: A schoolboy in post-war London stumbles on a criminal conspiracy whose members use his favourite comic strip to secretly send information to each other about their illegal activities. The police do not take him seriously, so he enlists his friends to help stop the crooks. Ealing comedy, starring Alastair Sim, Harry Fowler, Jack Warner and Valerie White(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.desc: For animals growing up is a real adventure, but finding food, avoiding predators and making friends doesn't always come naturally, so they need a little parental guidance to help them learn and hone the skills that will enable them to survive on their own. David Tennant narrates this documentary following the trials and tribulations of young animals all over the world as they prepare to leave home(n)

programme.title: Homes Under the Hammer
programme.desc: Developers Lucy Alexander and Martin Roberts are joined by former footballer Dion Dublin to explore properties about to be auctioned. They visit a three-bedroom semi in Crewe, a top-floor flat in London and a terrace house in Oldham. They then speak to the buyers about their plans, and find out how much they paid for them at auction(n)

programme.title: Two Greedy Italians
programme.sub-title: Two Greedy Italians: Still Hungry: Rome and Lazio and Machismo.
programme.desc: Chefs Antonio Carluccio and Gennaro Contaldo compare the traditional role of men in the mountain villages of Lazio to that of their counterparts in Rome. In the capital, the duo find that the masculine model of their youth is outworn, and discover that men are now willing to take on chores that were once considered outside their domain - including cooking. Featuring recipes for braised beef in red wine, sweet pepper omelette and bucatini pasta with bacon and chilli(n)

programme.title: Talking Pictures
programme.desc: Sylvia Syms revisits some of the great British war films that helped boost the nation's morale in the difficult years that followed the end of the Second World War. Among the silver screen gems highlighted are In Which We Serve, Reach for the Sky, Bridge on the River Kwai and The Dam Busters. The programme includes archive interviews with stars including Noel Coward, Richard Attenborough, David Lean, Alec Guinness, Kenneth More and John Mills, and Sylvia shares her memories of filming her own contribution to the genre, Ice Cold in Alex(n)

programme.title: The Wooden Horse
programme.desc: British PoWs in a German camp try to escape their captors by taking up gymnastics, and using a vaulting horse to conceal the tunnel they are digging. However, even if they manage to escape the camp, the journey to neutral territory will not be an easy one. Fact-based Second World War drama, starring Leo Genn, David Tomlinson, Anthony Steel and David Greene(n)

programme.title: Flog It
programme.desc: Paul Martin takes the antiques-selling show to the Kelvingrove Museum and Art Gallery in Glasgow, one of Scotland's most visited attractions(n)

programme.title: University Challenge
programme.desc: The quarter-finals conclude, with two teams of four students battling it out to make it to the next stage of the competition as they try to win a second match and progress to the semi-finals. Jeremy Paxman asks the questions(n)

programme.title: Only Connect
programme.desc: Victoria Coren Mitchell hosts the first semi-final, in which two teams of contenders use patience, lateral thinking and sheer inspiration to make connections between groups of four things that may appear at first not to be linked, with one set of clues consisting of Preion, Detive, Inenza and Eabeth(n)

programme.title: Gardeners' World
programme.desc: Monty starts his plans for his revamped courtyard garden, when he plants bare root trees and gives advice on climbers that will happily grow on east-facing walls. Nick Bailey explores the strange world of lichens and finds out how these plants grow and thrive on trees, wood and stone, while Frances Tophill meets the enthusiastic gardeners of Barbados who fill their gardens with colour, foliage and world class flowers. As part of the programmes 50th Anniversary, Flo Headlam reveals the plant she thinks has had the most impact on British gardens over the last half-century. Including weather(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.sub-title: Puerto Rico - Island of Enchantment: Natural World.
programme.desc: After being colonised by humans, Puerto Rico's rich natural resources were rapidly exploited for agriculture, industry and urban development - leading to 95 per cent of all its rainforests being lost. This documentary follows a conservation team fighting to save the most endangered creatures from extinction after they have been pushed to the edge of existence by human encroachment. David Attenborough narrates(n)

programme.title: Wild Ireland: The Edge of the World
programme.desc: Part two of two. Colin Stafford-Johnson heads north from Clew Bay for Donegal - golden eagle country - before reaching the island's northern tip and turning east along the coast of Northern Ireland. Along the way he observes the whooper swans that fly in every autumn to escape the Arctic winter and the elusive pine marten, an animal resident in the area since the last Ice Age. Basking sharks, bats and salmon are among the other creatures Colin comes across as he seeks out the remotest corners of Ireland's wild west(n)

programme.title: When Lynn Barber Met Phyllida Barlow
programme.desc: Veteran journalist Lynn Barber interviews sculptor and art teacher Phyllida Barlow, whose work has been selected to represent Britain at the 57th Venice International Biennale this year. While Barlow's work was largely ignored by curators and collectors until relatively recently, Barber first met the artist 30 years ago, when they were both young mothers in North London. Since then, Barlow has raised five children, and helped to inspire a generation of artists coming through London's various art schools, including Rachel Whiteread, the first woman to win the Turner Prize. Now, three decades after first entering Phyllida's house, Lynn returns to ask her old acquaintance about her experience of finding international art stardom in her 70s(n)

programme.title: Grand Tours of the Scottish Islands
programme.sub-title: From Flottay to Sanday: War and Peace in the North.
programme.desc: Paul Murton crosses the great natural harbour of Scapa Flow to the island of Flotta, before heading round the main Island of Orkney to Stronsay and on to the stunning beaches of Sanday. Along the way, he hears stories of the First World War, a mysterious beast and Orkney's selkies(n)

programme.title: Dad's Army
programme.desc: Mainwaring gives the platoon a lecture in communications and his men have an immediate opportunity to put what they have - or haven't - learnt into action when an enemy aircraft is forced to ditch in a reservoir near the town. Comedy first broadcast in 1969, starring Arthur Lowe, John Le Mesurier and Clive Dunn(n)

programme.title: Paula Rego: Secrets and Stories
programme.desc: Making use of new interviews and a vast archive of home video, film-maker Nick Willing compiles an intimate portrait of his mother, the celebrated painter Paula Rego. While Rego has been notoriously private and guarded about her personal life, she opens up to her son, discussing secrets and stories from her live, which has seen her battle fascism, misogyny in art world, and manic depression. Willing's film dictates his mother's story from her native Portugal, where she used her pictures as a weapon against dictatorship, through to settling in London, where she turned her craft toward tackling women's issues such as abortion rights(n)

programme.title: QI XL
programme.desc: Extended edition in which panellists Jo Brand, Bill Bailey, James Acaster and Alan Davies compete, as Stephen Fry mixes and matches a melange of M-subjects. As usual, the host poses questions that are so difficult, points are awarded for the answers he finds most interesting(n)

programme.title: Short Term 12
